lenders.name: Venus Factor Rocks
lenders.occupational_info:
What is the VF Program?

It is a concept that has been designed in accordance to eating, on certain days, a restricted caloric amount, thereby creating a “deficit.” On alternative days, however, you instead consume a little more, which is referred to as “maintenance.”

Thus, in essence, and just for example, for five, perhaps six days in the week, you’d consume less calories than what you’d burn, thereby generating the so-called deficit throughout most of the week. On the alternative day or days, you’d treat yourself to a well-deserved “break.” 

Nevertheless, quite unlike so many other dieting plans, the key concept with the Venus Factor program is that your body becomes used to a “normal” caloric intake – a caloric intake that is best suited in terms of your body type and your system. What’s the purpose of this? It works to the effect that you never gain back the weight that you’ve already shed. You can learn more about this here: http://www.venusfactor.rocks. 

Though the VF Program endorses what appear to be some rather extreme workouts, they are not quite as tiring as you likely expect. In truth, you will feel fatigued, and that’s exactly what’s meant to happen. However, the exercises have a short duration, and only around 15 minutes is required to complete them each day. 

With the Program, you’ll receive a few videos that dictate the exercise philosophies and strategies. You also get a couple of weights – plenty light enough to be able to utilize within the exercise program. And providing you have a TV/ computer from which to watch the exercises, along with a bit of space, you’re good to go. 

It’s advisable to give yourself around 12 weeks in all, so as to really get to grips with the exercises that are part and parcel of the Venus Program. There’s a definite potential to struggle in the early days where the reduced caloric intake is concerned. After all, this is quite an unnatural scenario for your body. And in all likelihood, your mind and body will aim to fight against this deficit, and there will be times when food cravings are extreme. 

Nevertheless, again, it takes time to adapt. By all means, seek the support of a friend, a spouse, a further family member – anyone who will help you to remain focused and will push you along whenever you feel the need for it. 

It’s true that before I started the Venus Program, I was particularly skeptical. I was concerned about the exercises, since my lifestyle had rarely involved much in the way of physical exercise. But I was even more concerned about the regular calorie deficit. How would I cope with that?

All the same, I stuck with it, as much hardship as there was, and it’s certainly paid off handsomely. Thus, if you too want for a healthier metabolism, a more balanced hormonal system, along with the asset of a beautifully toned body, then I’d suggest that the Venus Program is a valid choice for you.
